HOUSE JOINT RESOLUTION 1132
By Gant
A RESOLUTION to honor and congratulate Novella Morrow on the
occasion of her 102nd birthday.
WHEREAS, it is fitting that the members of this General Assembly pay tribute to those
citizens who are celebrating special occasions in their estimable lives; and
WHEREAS, Novella Morrow will celebrate her 102nd birthday on April 17, 2026, a
milestone that will be commemorated as yet another precious souvenir of life's rich pageant;
and
WHEREAS, the daughter of L.B. Avant and Darlene Avant, Novella Morrow was born in
the Ames Plantation community; and
WHEREAS, Mother Novella Morrow is the fifth of nine children, six of whom are
deceased; her siblings who are still living include Ida Lee Peeler and Melroy Avant, and her
deceased siblings are Everlyn Waddell, Willie B. Avant, Emma Sue Smith, Elizabeth Scott
Heard, Ocdell Hussey, and Ellie B. Anderson; and
WHEREAS, Mother Morrow was married to the late A.D. Morrow for fifty years; she has
three children, Mary, Mattie, and Margaret; her four grandchildren are Pamela, Kimberly,
Tyrone, and Quartella (Nicolas); her seven great-grandchildren are Brandon (Shay), Bria (Jay),
Paige, Nicolas, Jr., Anterrious (Aerial), Antonio, and Anterrica; and her six great-great-
grandchildren are Karson, Ari, Tvarsky, King, Kadence, and Korbin; and
WHEREAS, Mother Morrow was baptized at an early age at Jones Chapel Missionary
Baptist Church under the leadership of Pastor Robert Branch; and
WHEREAS, today, Mother Morrow faithfully attends Sunday School, is an active
member of the Mother Board, and regularly attends the Fayette County Commission on Aging
Center; and
HJR1132
015538
- 1 -

WHEREAS, Mother Morrow, throughout her life, has exemplified true Christian
character: a quiet spirit, love, joy, peace, kindness, goodness, and meekness. She is so faithful
that she has never missed a church event. She loves traveling and enjoying herself; and
WHEREAS, as she enjoys this great milestone in her life, Mother Morrow continues to
be a blessing to her family and the Jones Chapel Church family; and
WHEREAS, we wish to grasp this golden opportunity to specially recognize one of
Tennessee's most outstanding citizens on this very special occasion; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE ONE HUNDRED
FOURTEENTH GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE SENATE
CONCURRING, that we honor Novella Morrow on the occasion of her 102nd birthday and
extend to her our warmest wishes for many happy returns of the day.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
the appropriate clerk, the language appearing immediately following the State seal appear
without House or Senate designation.
